Title: Noncommutative gravity: fuzzy sphere and others
Authors: Yasuhiro Abe and V.P. Nair
Comments: LaTeX, 11 pages
Report-no: CCNY-HEP-5/02
\\
  Gravity on noncommutative analogues of compact spaces can give a finite mode
truncation of ordinary commutative gravity. We obtain the action for gravity on
the noncommutative two-sphere in terms of finite dimensional $(N\times
N)$-matrices and discuss the commutative large $N$ limit.
